  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I restore misc files from phone?",
  "response": "Restoring miscellaneous files from a phone can depend on several factors, including the phone's operating system, whether you have backups, and the specific file types you're trying to recover. Here's a general guide to help you retrieve these files:\n\n### For Android Devices:\n\n1. **Check Google Drive:**\n   - If you have been using Google Backup, your files might be stored there. Open Google Drive and check if your files are available.\n\n2. **File Manager:**\n   - Sometimes, files may be misplaced. Use a file manager app to search for the files. Navigate through the folders and check the \"Downloads,\" \"Documents,\" or any other relevant folders.\n\n3. **Recover from MicroSD Card:**\n   - If your files were stored on a microSD card, you can insert it into a computer and use data recovery software like Recuva or EaseUS to scan and recover deleted files.\n\n4. **Data Recovery Apps:**\n   - There are various apps like DiskDigger or Dr.Fone that can help recover deleted files. Install one and follow the instructions to attempt recovery.\n\n5. **Cloud Services:**\n   - If you use any cloud services (like Dropbox, OneDrive), check them for backups or copies of your misc files.\n\n### For iOS Devices:\n\n1. **iCloud Backup:**\n   - If your files were backed up to iCloud, you can restore your phone from an iCloud backup. Go to `Settings` > `General` > `Reset` > `Erase All Content and Settings`, and then follow the on-screen instructions to restore from an iCloud backup.\n\n2. **iTunes Backup:**\n   - If you have backed up your phone to a computer using iTunes, you can restore from there. Connect your device to the computer, open iTunes, select your device, and choose \"Restore Backup.\"\n\n3. **File App:**\n   - Use the Files app on your iPhone to search for any misplaced files that might have been saved in another location on your device.\n\n4. **Data Recovery Software:**\n   - Use data recovery software like PhoneRescue or Dr.Fone for iOS, which can scan your phone and help recover deleted files.\n\n### General Tips:\n\n- **Regular Backups:**\n  - To prevent future data loss, regularly back up your phone's data using cloud services or local backups.\n\n- **Avoid Overwriting:**\n  - Limit the use of your phone immediately after data loss to prevent new data from overwriting the deleted files.\n\n- **Seek Professional Help:**\n  - If the data is highly valuable and difficult to recover, consider professional data recovery services.\n\nPlease note that data recovery has varying success rates depending on how the data was deleted and the time elapsed since deletion.",
